<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>Myles Braithwaite: weblog entries tagged in iWork.</title><link>http://mylesbraithwaite.com/blog/tag/iWork/</link><description>Hoping for the Best, Imagining the Worst.</description><atom:link href="http://mylesbraithwaite.com/feeds/blog/tag/iwork/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en-ca</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 31 May 2011 13:49:00 -0400</lastBuildDate><item><title>Writing a Letter in iWork Pages</title><link>http://mylesbraithwaite.com/blog/2011/may/31/iwork-iphone/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Apple released &lt;a href="http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2011/05/31iwork.html" title="Apple iWork Now Available For iPhone &amp;amp; iPod touch Users"&gt;iWork&lt;/a&gt; (Pages, Keynote, and Numbers) for the iPhone (and iPod Touch) today and coincidentally I had to write an actually print on a dead tree, lick a stamp, and put in an envelope letter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="illustration inline"&gt;
&lt;a data-toggle="lightbox" href="//media.mylesbraithwaite.com/attachments/blog_post/43/iwork_pages-large.png" title="Pages (iWork) for Apple's iPhone 4"&gt;
&lt;img alt="Pages (iWork) for Apple's iPhone 4" src="http://media.mylesbraithwaite.com/attachments/blog_post/43/iwork_pages-small.png"&gt;
&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It a decent enough word processor but I still prefer using &lt;a href="http://www.secondgearsoftware.com/elements/" title="Elements - Dropbox powered text editor for iPhone, iPad and iPod touch from Second Gear"&gt;Elements&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/"&gt;Markdown&lt;/a&gt; (I am now using &lt;a href="http://www.iawriter.com/"&gt;iA Writer&lt;/a&gt; on my &lt;a href="http://www.iawriter.com/mac" title="iA Writer for Mac OS X"&gt;Mac&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://www.iawriter.com/ipad" title="iA Writer for iPad"&gt;iPad&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description><author>me@mylesbraithwaite.com (Myles Braithwaite)</author><pubDate>Tue, 31 May 2011 13:49:00 -0400</pubDate><guid>http://mylesbraithwaite.com/blog/2011/may/31/iwork-iphone/</guid><enclosure url="http://media.mylesbraithwaite.com/attachments/blog_post/43/iwork_pages-small.png" length="None" type="image/png"></enclosure><category>iPhone</category><category>iWork</category><category>Apple</category></item></channel></rss>